  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Lebanon Security Programme</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This programme is addressing three key strands of overlapping security threats in Lebanon.  The programme supports (1) The establishment and deployment of Land Border Regiments of the Lebanese Armed Forces (LAF) to monitor and interdict illegal cross border activity along the northern and eastern border between Lebanon and Syria. (2) Aims to build the capability of the Internal Security Forces toward an improved service of internal security provision, including fostering more effective cooperation with other security institutions. (3) The work on countering violent extremism is addressing threats emerging from vulnerable communities by de-conflicting these communities and de-radicalising those at risk. This is an ODA and non-ODA integrated programme. The spend reported against this programme is the ODA element alone.</narrative>
  </description>
